First Lady Melania Trump accompanied President Trump on a state visit to Tokyo, Japan. Upon arrival, they were greeted by the Japanese delegation. Mrs. Trump later joined Mrs. Abe, the spouse of Japan's Prime Minister, on a tour of the teamLab Borderless Exhibit at the Mori Building Digital Art Museum. This made her the first US First Lady to visit the museum. They explored various exhibits, including a flower room, waterfall room, crystal room, cave room, lamp room, and landscape exhibit, all featuring light shows and interactive demonstrations. The tour ended at a digital aquarium where children drew sea animals and scanned them into a computer that projected them onto the walls. Mrs. Trump and Mrs. Abe joined the children in designing sea creature creations. They also had tea in the Tea House exhibit before leaving. In the evening, they attended a sumo wrestling championship match and concluded the day with a private dinner.